snippet.textDisplay: Here's a solution for all of General Motors' many problems. Take the designers and engineers associated with the Corvette and put them in charge of the entire GM lineup. Not because every vehicle should be a Corvette clone but because the new Corvette demonstrates the ability to hit a design/engineering target at a particular price point. The result is an extraordinary value proposition. Hyundai/KIA has shown what  imaginative and  competent management/design/engineering teams can do to produce an entire range of outstanding vehicles. GM doesn't have to import such individuals from outside the company. They've already proven what they can do with the Corvette.

snippet.textDisplay: Chevy has kept the sports car at a nice price since 1953 (that's 67 years to you and me).  They have always been putting cutting edge tech in the everyday drive sports car all of which is attainable unlike the others like the lambos first production car 1967, and mclarens first production car 1992.  Just take a look at the website and see all that is offered on a base model.  They do such an awesome job at getting so much to the consumer for the price.  The quality of the car just goes up and up.  It is an everyday super ride.  It looks awesome too.  Those others are playing catch up to the corvette.  They don't cater to the everyday man but Chevy Corvette is the everyday man's sports car company and they have been working giving that man for the last 67 years the opportunity to purchase an awesome US made sports car at a reasonable price.
